  "body": "### Component\n\nForge, Cast, Anvil\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nRight now most (all?) addresses printed to the terminal are lowercased. Often I want to copy that address in solidity, which requires checksummed addresses, so I need to checksum it manually using e.g. `cast --to-checksum-address`.\r\n\r\nIn general, some tools/apps require checksum addresses, some support both, and I've never seen one that requires lowercase. So in my opinion always using checksum addresses is more convenient without any downsides.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
